{% comment %}
  sections/homepage-products.liquid
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Jedi homepage featured products section.

  Pulls the first 4 products from the light-side collection and displays
  them in a horizontally scrollable card row.

  Key Liquid concepts used here:
    - collections['handle']  → access a collection by its URL handle
    - for product in ...     → loop over each product
    - limit: 4               → stop after 4 products
    - product.title          → the product's name
    - product.price          → price in cents — use | money to format it
    - product.url            → the product's page URL
    - product.featured_image → the product's main image

  Structure:
    <section>                ← full-width products block
      <div> inner            ← centers content, caps max-width
        <div> heading        ← eyebrow + title
        <div> track          ← horizontal scroll container
          <div> card × 4    ← one card per product (Liquid loop)
            <div> image      ← product image
            <p>   name       ← product.title
            <p>   price      ← product.price | money
            <a>   button     ← links to product page
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %} Load this section's stylesheet {% endcomment %}
{{ 'homepage-products.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

{% comment %}
  Assign the light-side collection to a variable so we can loop over it.
  Using a variable keeps the code clean — we only reference the collection handle once.
{% endcomment %}
{% assign featured = collections['light-side'] %}

<section class="gf-products" aria-label="Featured Products">

  <div class="gf-products__inner">

    {% comment %} Section heading — same eyebrow + title pattern as categories {% endcomment %}
    <div class="gf-products__heading">
      <p class="gf-products__eyebrow">From the Vault</p>
      <h2 class="gf-products__title">Featured Artifacts</h2>
    </div>

    {% comment %}
      Scroll track — this div overflows horizontally.
      Cards sit inside it in a row and the visitor scrolls to see them all.
    {% endcomment %}
    <div class="gf-products__track">

      {% comment %}
        Loop over the first 4 products in the light-side collection.
        Inside the loop, `product` refers to the current product.
      {% endcomment %}
      {% for product in featured.products limit: 5 %}

        <div class="gf-product-card">

          {% comment %}
            Product image.
            featured_image gives us the main product image.
            | image_url: width: 600 tells Shopify to serve a 600px wide version.
            | image_tag renders the full <img> tag with src, alt, width, height.
            If no image exists we show a plain placeholder div instead.
          {% endcomment %}
          <div class="gf-product-card__img">
            {% if product.featured_image %}
              {{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 600 | image_tag: alt: product.title, loading: 'lazy' }}
            {% else %}
              <div class="gf-product-card__img-placeholder"></div>
            {% endif %}
          </div>

          {% comment %} Product name {% endcomment %}
          <p class="gf-product-card__name">{{ product.title }}</p>

          {% comment %}
            Product price.
            product.price is stored in cents (e.g. 4999 for $49.99).
            The | money filter converts it to the store's currency format automatically.
          {% endcomment %}
          <p class="gf-product-card__price">{{ product.price | money }}</p>

          {% comment %}
            Shop Now button — links directly to the product page.
            product.url gives us the correct URL for this product.
          {% endcomment %}
          <a href="{{ product.url }}" class="gf-product-card__btn">Shop Now</a>

        </div>

      {% endfor %}

    </div>

  </div>

</section>
